<subSubSection lastPageId="37" lastPageNumber="38" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1436,1945,2044]" box="[151,586,1945,1972]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,530,1945,1972]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Number of specimens recorded.</emphasis>
263.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1436,1945,2044]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1981,2008]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Distribution.</emphasis>
Southwestern European distribution (
<collectingCountry box="[786,854,1982,2008]" name="Spain" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Spain</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[868,966,1982,2008]" name="Portugal" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Portugal</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[979,1060,1983,2009]" name="France" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">France</collectingCountry>
); also North Africa. 
<collectingCountry box="[1296,1395,1982,2008]" name="Portugal" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Portugal</collectingCountry>
: 10 provinces (see also 
<bibRefCitation author="Naglis, S. &amp; Bartak, M." box="[371,623,2017,2044]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="125 - 137" refId="ref33294" refString="Naglis, S. &amp; Bartak, M. (2015) Dolichopodidae (Diptera) from the Iberian Peninsula, with description of three new species. Zootaxa, 3964 (1), 125 - 137. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3964.1.9" type="journal article" year="2015">Naglis &amp; Barták 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,153,395]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,153,179]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Ecology.</emphasis>
Though being collected in all macrohabitat categories except for mountainous biotopes, this species seems to prefer agricultural land, marshlands and banks of water bodies. It has been collected abundantly in 
<collectingCountry box="[1341,1436,189,215]" name="Portugal" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Portugal</collectingCountry>
at seepages in mixed forest and on pebbly river banks. This species is not recorded from northwestern Europe.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,153,395]" box="[199,525,260,287]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,260,287]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Rarity (%).</emphasis>
29.9 (common).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,153,395]" box="[199,517,296,323]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,386,296,323]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Activity period.</emphasis>
April–July.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,153,395]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,333,359]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Remarks.</emphasis>
Czech specimens identified as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Olejnicek &amp; Bartak 2000)" authorityName="Olejnicek &amp; Bartak" authorityYear="2000" baseAuthorityName="Olejnicek &amp; Bartak" baseAuthorityYear="2000" box="[678,1202,333,359]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="appendiculatus">
<emphasis box="[678,885,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">H. appendiculatus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Olejnicek, J. &amp; Bartak, M." box="[902,1195,333,359]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="191 - 199" refId="ref33946" refString="Olejnicek, J. &amp; Bartak, M. (2000) Dolichopodidae. In: Bartak, M. &amp; Vanhara, J. (Eds.), Diptera in an Industrially Affected Region (North-Western Bohemia, Bilina and Duchcov Environs). I. Folia Facultatis Scientiarium Naturalium Universitatis Masarykianae Brunensis, Biologia, 104, 191 - 199." type="journal article" year="2000">Olejnicek &amp; Barták 2000</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
proved to belong to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mik" authorityYear="1878" box="[151,322,369,395]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Poecilobothrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,322,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Poecilobothrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which renders its occurrence in the 
<collectingCountry box="[734,912,369,395]" name="Czech Republic" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Czech Republic</collectingCountry>
erroneous.
</paragraph>
